WEBVTT

00:05.642 --> 00:07.242
ST. JOHN HUNT:
♪ <i>MacArthur's Park ♪</i>

00:07.242 --> 00:09.978
<i>♪ Is melting in the dark ♪</i>

00:09.978 --> 00:15.250
♪ <i>All the sweet
Green icing flowing down ♪</i>

00:15.250 --> 00:17.656
You and I need to talk...

00:19.090 --> 00:20.525
before the trial.

00:21.426 --> 00:24.326
Not now.

00:24.326 --> 00:27.328
ST. JOHN: ♪ <i>Because it took
So long to bake it ♪</i>

00:27.328 --> 00:31.803
<i>♪ And I'll never have
That recipe again ♪</i>

00:33.171 --> 00:37.109
<i>♪ I recall the yellow
Cotton dress ♪</i>

00:37.775 --> 00:41.010
<i>♪ Foaming like a wave ♪</i>

00:41.010 --> 00:43.712
<i>♪ On the ground
Around her knees ♪</i>

00:43.712 --> 00:46.681
<i>- ♪ The birds... ♪</i>
- There are a couple of things

00:46.681 --> 00:50.289
that we need to sort out
about Watergate, pronto.

00:53.024 --> 00:57.292
- Like the book.
- Not now. Later.

00:57.292 --> 01:03.268
<i>♪ Is melting in the dark
All the sweet green icing ♪</i>

01:04.135 --> 01:06.468
<i>♪ Flowing down ♪</i>

01:06.468 --> 01:09.608
- (SOBS)
- LISA HUNT: Sit down.

01:10.975 --> 01:12.540
Go sit down. It's okay.

01:12.540 --> 01:14.476
- ♪ (SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
- Later, when?

01:14.476 --> 01:16.445
PRIEST: Bless this gravestone
with which we mark

01:16.445 --> 01:19.715
the resting place
of Dorothy Wetzel Hunt.

01:19.715 --> 01:20.785
Amen.

01:25.490 --> 01:28.493
(BOTH SOB)

01:31.128 --> 01:32.464
My condolences.

01:34.232 --> 01:37.736
♪ ("WHITE HOUSE PLUMBERS"
THEME MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

01:42.540 --> 01:44.840
♪ (THEME MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

01:44.840 --> 01:46.374
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

01:46.374 --> 01:49.644
CHAPMAN: We're so sorry for you
and the family.

01:49.644 --> 01:51.513
MOURNER:
Everyone really loved Dorothy.

01:51.513 --> 01:53.381
- Tough break, Howard.
- Thank you.

01:53.381 --> 01:55.717
- (RAIN PATTERING)
- Thank you.

01:55.717 --> 01:58.186
WILLIAM F. BUCKLEY JR.:
Howard. Dear Kevan.

01:58.186 --> 02:01.589
My profound and fathomless condolences.

02:01.589 --> 02:04.829
Howard, Dorothy
was a classy lady.

02:05.329 --> 02:06.727
Thank you, Doctor.

02:06.727 --> 02:08.263
- (DR. MANUEL ARTIME
SPEAKING SPANISH)
- (IN ENGLISH) Bill.

02:08.263 --> 02:09.768
She's in a better place.

02:11.568 --> 02:13.505
E. HOWARD HUNT:
Thank you for coming.

02:15.106 --> 02:16.675
Who was that with Mr. Buckley?

02:17.709 --> 02:20.275
Dr. Artime. Uh...

02:20.275 --> 02:22.410
If Kennedy had done
his goddamn job,

02:22.410 --> 02:25.581
he'd be president
of Cuba, right now.

02:25.581 --> 02:27.252
I'm so sorry dear.

02:31.956 --> 02:33.592
(SIGHS)

02:41.432 --> 02:45.067
Your father is having
a rough time right now.

02:45.067 --> 02:46.705
Because of your mother.

02:47.606 --> 02:49.674
She bought me my first guitar.

02:50.407 --> 02:52.307
G. GORDON LIDDY: Hmm.

02:52.307 --> 02:55.280
I was so scared to play it
for him. (WHIMPERS)

02:57.381 --> 03:00.419
Fear is a powerful tool.

03:01.352 --> 03:03.285
When I was young...

03:03.285 --> 03:07.288
I was afraid of everything.
Rats in particular.

03:07.288 --> 03:09.361
But one day when I was ten...

03:10.428 --> 03:14.499
I cornered the biggest rat
that I could find.

03:17.902 --> 03:19.199
And I killed it.

03:21.138 --> 03:22.407
Then cooked it.

03:24.342 --> 03:25.877
And I ate it.

03:27.644 --> 03:30.882
And after that, rats
did not bother me anymore.

03:36.186 --> 03:38.657
Face your fears, son.

03:42.359 --> 03:46.161
Has your father mentioned
any new books

03:46.161 --> 03:47.699
that he's been writing?

03:48.432 --> 03:50.469
- (DRINK POURING)
- What?

03:52.671 --> 03:53.805
Howard.

03:55.205 --> 03:58.640
- Fran.
- FRAN LIDDY: How are the kids?

03:58.640 --> 04:00.741
Do you need an extra hand?
I can come by?

04:00.741 --> 04:06.248
I'm flying up the woman
who lived with us in Uruguay

04:06.248 --> 04:10.118
- to help with David.
- It must be so overwhelming.

04:10.118 --> 04:13.956
Never in my worst nightmares...

04:13.956 --> 04:18.898
would I have imagined
my own country turning on me.

04:20.899 --> 04:22.330
(BREATHES SHAKILY)

04:22.330 --> 04:24.970
- I might go to jail.
- Yes.

04:26.170 --> 04:29.641
It is awful. Just awful.

04:32.744 --> 04:34.609
But I meant David.

04:34.609 --> 04:38.580
Oh, right. The boy, uh,
of course. What...

04:38.580 --> 04:42.284
Uh, David will be looked after.

04:42.284 --> 04:44.687
When I was pregnant
with our fourth,

04:44.687 --> 04:46.755
Gordon came home
and found me standing

04:46.755 --> 04:50.059
in the doorway banging my head
against the door frame.

04:50.059 --> 04:51.359
I was dog tired.

04:51.359 --> 04:55.463
I didn't think I'd survive,
but here I am.

04:55.463 --> 04:58.399
You'll find a way.
Just take care of the children.

04:58.399 --> 05:00.636
Suppose if I was married
to Gordon,

05:00.636 --> 05:02.938
I would bang my head
against the door

05:02.938 --> 05:05.174
from time to time.

05:05.174 --> 05:08.308
- (DOORBELL RINGING)
- (BOTH LAUGH)

05:10.448 --> 05:13.085
- I needed a laugh.
- (FRAN LAUGHS)

05:14.552 --> 05:16.888
- (DOORBELL RINGING)
- Excuse me.

05:21.259 --> 05:23.759
Are you deaf? Answer
the goddamn door!

05:23.759 --> 05:25.060
- (DOORBELL RINGING)
- Excuse him.

05:25.060 --> 05:26.431
HOWARD: I'm coming!

05:30.434 --> 05:33.572
- Your father is--
- An asshole.

05:35.073 --> 05:36.336
He's scared.

05:37.007 --> 05:38.944
Fear is a powerful tool.

05:41.345 --> 05:42.847
Are you afraid of rats?

05:46.550 --> 05:48.516
- Jim.
- JAMES W. MCCORD: Howard.

05:48.516 --> 05:50.720
Oh, I'm sorry for the intrusion
but I came to pay

05:50.720 --> 05:52.320
my condolences.

05:52.320 --> 05:54.589
The wife made you
a little something.

05:54.589 --> 05:57.930
I figured nobody's doing
any cooking around here.

05:59.797 --> 06:01.133
- Tuna.
- Hmm.

06:02.200 --> 06:04.700
Well, thanks, Jim.

06:04.700 --> 06:07.572
You know,
that Dorothy's a fine woman.

06:08.105 --> 06:09.638
- She was.
- Yeah.

06:09.638 --> 06:11.372
Did you see that Nixon named

06:11.372 --> 06:14.142
a new undersecretary
of transportation?

06:14.142 --> 06:17.480
One of his boys, uh,
Egil Krogh?

06:17.480 --> 06:19.518
- Bud Krogh?
- Oh, yeah.

06:21.152 --> 06:22.317
I hadn't heard that.

06:22.317 --> 06:24.619
You see, it turns out
now this Krogh fella

06:24.619 --> 06:28.893
has oversight over all FAA
and NTSB investigations,

06:29.660 --> 06:31.730
uh, including plane crashes.

06:33.532 --> 06:34.833
Funny, huh?

06:37.701 --> 06:41.773
I-- I-- I'm sure,
it's a coincidence.

06:42.273 --> 06:43.542
MCCORD: Of course.

06:44.108 --> 06:46.474
It's just a coincidence.

06:46.474 --> 06:49.311
All right, Howard, I'll see you
at the courthouse.

06:49.311 --> 06:52.413
- Thanks, Jim.
- Oh, not for nothing,

06:52.413 --> 06:56.351
but could you return that empty
casserole dish?

06:56.351 --> 06:58.687
Uh, it is my wife's favorite.

06:58.687 --> 07:01.526
- You bet, Jim.
- Well, thank you, Howard.

07:02.926 --> 07:05.797
- ♪ (SOFT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
- (INDISTINCT CHATTER)

07:09.533 --> 07:11.603
(DR. ARTIME SPEAKING SPANISH)

07:16.808 --> 07:17.977
(IN ENGLISH) Hello, David.

07:18.343 --> 07:19.511
Hey.

07:21.480 --> 07:23.378
DR. ARTIME: David?

07:23.378 --> 07:25.884
Do you know what a godfather
does?

07:26.417 --> 07:27.249
No.

07:27.249 --> 07:30.318
If anything should happen
to your father,

07:30.318 --> 07:32.057
I will be your father.

07:32.791 --> 07:33.825
Okay?

07:37.095 --> 07:38.197
DAVID HUNT: Lisa!

07:42.299 --> 07:43.602
LIDDY: Finally!

07:44.869 --> 07:46.671
You think it's safe to talk?

07:48.873 --> 07:51.072
Unless those birds
are federal agents,

07:51.072 --> 07:52.340
I'd say it's safe.

07:52.340 --> 07:55.144
Did you know that Dorothy
took out

07:55.144 --> 07:57.780
a two-hundred-thousand-dollar
life insurance policy

07:57.780 --> 08:00.953
right before she stepped
on that plane?

08:02.153 --> 08:03.822
- Yeah.
- Given the...

08:04.521 --> 08:06.926
influx of insurance money,

08:07.625 --> 08:09.861
I'm hoping you have...

08:11.029 --> 08:13.863
considered not doing
some of the things

08:13.863 --> 08:15.234
that you were...

08:17.968 --> 08:20.368
- you know, considering doing.
- For Christ's sake, Gordon,

08:20.368 --> 08:22.872
I'm not writing
the fucking book!

08:22.872 --> 08:26.506
- Is that why you came?
- No! No.

08:28.079 --> 08:31.847
Her plane got rerouted
at the last minute

08:31.847 --> 08:35.154
they turned off
the runway lights.

08:35.854 --> 08:38.954
The FBI beat the firemen there.

08:38.954 --> 08:42.690
They beat them there, Gordon.
Dozens of agents!

08:42.690 --> 08:46.762
- (SHUSHES) Calm down.
- Yeah, but don't you see?

08:46.762 --> 08:49.431
The firemen always
get there first.

08:49.431 --> 08:51.766
And then they call the NTSB.

08:51.766 --> 08:57.440
And if and only if the NTSB
finds anything suspicious

08:57.440 --> 08:59.507
do they call the FBI.

08:59.507 --> 09:02.711
So, how the hell
did the FBI get there first?

09:02.711 --> 09:04.879
So, you think that the FBI
took down

09:04.879 --> 09:09.919
an entire United Airlines 737
just to shut you up

09:09.919 --> 09:11.156
about Watergate?

09:11.922 --> 09:14.326
Not just Watergate, Gordon.

09:15.892 --> 09:20.462
- I said some things.
- Why not just kill you, hmm?

09:20.462 --> 09:23.131
Hell, thought's occurred
to me several times.

09:23.131 --> 09:26.567
Did Dot sense something
or did she see someone?

09:26.567 --> 09:29.204
Why the hell did she take out
the insurance?

09:29.204 --> 09:33.575
- Howard, take a deep breath.
- (BREATHES DEEPLY)

09:33.575 --> 09:37.616
You're my friend.
And you have to stay strong.

09:39.016 --> 09:43.622
We need to leave this meeting
on the same page.

09:44.188 --> 09:45.585
<i>¿Comprende?</i>

09:50.594 --> 09:52.297
(IN ENGLISH)
This isn't a meeting, Gordon,

09:53.164 --> 09:54.266
It's a funeral.

10:07.212 --> 10:08.608
(SIGHS)

10:15.954 --> 10:16.989
(GRUNTS)

10:46.217 --> 10:51.386
- All packed up for the morning?
- You know, I don't have to go.

10:51.386 --> 10:54.089
Sweetie, I think your mother
would want at least

10:54.089 --> 10:58.626
- one of her kids to graduate.
- (CHUCKLES)

10:58.626 --> 11:01.400
- You okay, Papa?
- There's something...

11:02.700 --> 11:04.869
of your mother's I have.

11:05.670 --> 11:07.872
Her camel hair coat?

11:08.507 --> 11:09.942
No. That...

11:10.742 --> 11:12.344
she was wearing on the plane.

11:23.422 --> 11:24.389
Never mind.

11:25.490 --> 11:26.458
Good night.

11:27.224 --> 11:28.260
What is that?

11:29.193 --> 11:30.625
Nothing.

11:30.625 --> 11:32.628
Well, if it belonged to Mama,
I want it.

11:32.628 --> 11:34.730
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

11:34.730 --> 11:35.968
What is it?

11:41.339 --> 11:43.404
I can't tell you.

11:43.404 --> 11:47.943
I will simply say this.
What's inside this envelope

11:47.943 --> 11:51.783
could be dangerous
to what's left of this family.

11:52.316 --> 11:53.485
I don't understand.

11:54.318 --> 11:55.383
Then destroy it.

11:55.383 --> 12:00.792
I need to be able to say
under oath that I didn't.

12:01.893 --> 12:05.560
Do you want me to destroy it?

12:05.560 --> 12:07.799
I can't tell you
to do that either.

12:08.599 --> 12:11.236
You're the only one
I can trust.

12:14.739 --> 12:16.508
Only you, pumpkin.

12:22.146 --> 12:24.516
- Goodnight.
- Goodnight, Papa.

12:30.955 --> 12:37.955
♪ (MUSIC TURNS SINISTER,
FADES) ♪

12:38.062 --> 12:40.195
- (INTERCOM BEEPS)
- SECRETARY: <i>Mr. Dean?</i>

12:40.195 --> 12:43.002
<i>Someone claiming to be
George McGovern is on the phone.</i>

12:45.269 --> 12:46.271
Put him through.

12:46.771 --> 12:48.373
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

12:50.375 --> 12:51.739
Gordon.

12:51.739 --> 12:55.110
I have serious concerns
about Hunt's stability.

12:55.110 --> 12:57.312
I don't know how long
he can take the pressure

12:57.312 --> 12:59.480
without cracking.
What can I bring him

12:59.480 --> 13:01.583
to tide him over, calm him down?

13:01.583 --> 13:03.085
Just tell I'm taking care of it.

13:03.085 --> 13:04.787
The-- the Plumbers will get
living expenses

13:04.787 --> 13:07.790
of 30,000 per annum,
plus legal fees.

13:07.790 --> 13:09.525
And, uh...

13:09.525 --> 13:11.259
you'll do time, but at Danbury.

13:11.259 --> 13:13.328
Not bad. How long?

13:13.328 --> 13:16.165
Uh, you'll get
a presidential pardon within

13:16.165 --> 13:17.933
- two years.
- LIDDY: <i>Right.</i>

13:17.933 --> 13:19.438
Just so we're clear...

13:20.605 --> 13:22.137
I am a soldier.

13:22.137 --> 13:24.039
And I can keep my mouth shut
no matter what.

13:24.039 --> 13:26.008
But I'm not sure two years
is gonna cut it for Hunt.

13:26.008 --> 13:28.077
JOHN DEAN: <i>I don't know
what you expect me to do.</i>

13:28.077 --> 13:30.446
There are limits
to what is possible,

13:30.446 --> 13:31.713
given the circumstances.

13:31.713 --> 13:33.052
Understood.

13:34.152 --> 13:36.318
Should, um... (CLICKS TONGUE)

13:36.318 --> 13:39.487
...prophylactic action
need to be taken?

13:39.487 --> 13:41.122
Wh-- what are you talking about?

13:41.122 --> 13:44.326
To ensure
his enduring silence.

13:44.326 --> 13:47.830
I am prepared to use any
and all means and methods

13:47.830 --> 13:49.301
at my disposal.

13:49.901 --> 13:51.566
Think about it.

13:51.566 --> 13:54.670
- I will wait for a signal.
- What?

13:54.670 --> 13:55.838
Is that the signal?

13:55.838 --> 13:57.539
DEAN: <i>Do not break
another goddamn law.</i>

13:57.539 --> 14:00.175
Not a parking ticket.
No jaywalking. Understood?

14:00.175 --> 14:02.705
See if you can do better
than two years.

14:02.705 --> 14:06.214
Remember, you're in deeper shit
than we are.

14:06.214 --> 14:08.750
We just planted a few bugs.
All that money you gave us?

14:08.750 --> 14:10.385
That is some
big-time obstruction

14:10.385 --> 14:12.958
for the White House.
That is a federal--

14:13.692 --> 14:14.856
Hello?

14:14.856 --> 14:16.224
I'm heading over
to the West Wing.

14:16.224 --> 14:18.193
Tell them I need five minutes
with the president.

14:18.193 --> 14:21.033
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

14:21.632 --> 14:23.402
Fucking little prick!

14:27.304 --> 14:29.170
RICHARD NIXON:
<i>Under my direction, uh,</i>

14:29.170 --> 14:31.206
<i>counsel to the president,
Mr. Dean,</i>

14:31.206 --> 14:33.909
<i>has conducted
a complete investigation</i>

14:33.909 --> 14:37.145
<i>of all leads
which might involve any</i>

14:37.145 --> 14:39.014
<i>or anybody in the government.</i>

14:39.014 --> 14:42.217
<i>And I can say categorically
that his investigation</i>

14:42.217 --> 14:45.120
<i>indicates that no one
in the White House staff,</i>

14:45.120 --> 14:49.357
<i>no one in this administration,
presently employed,</i>

14:49.357 --> 14:53.995
<i>uh, was involved
in this very bizarre incident.</i>

14:53.995 --> 14:55.891
<i>The trial
of those formally charged</i>

14:55.891 --> 14:57.532
<i>with breaking into
Democratic Party headquarters</i>

14:57.532 --> 15:00.836
<i>is about to start.
Daniel Schorr reports.</i>

15:00.836 --> 15:02.237
DANIEL SCHORR:
<i>From the Watergate building</i>

15:02.237 --> 15:04.272
<i>two miles away
to this federal courthouse</i>

15:04.272 --> 15:06.842
<i>has stretched a six-month road, detouring</i>

15:06.842 --> 15:08.772
<i>through sensational
newspaper reports</i>

15:08.772 --> 15:10.980
<i>and the presidential
election campaign.</i>

15:10.980 --> 15:13.581
<i>So this could be a trial
of just seven men</i>

15:13.581 --> 15:16.585
<i>or it could develop
into a political sensation.</i>

15:16.585 --> 15:19.554
<i>It promises at any rate
to be the greatest drama</i>

15:19.554 --> 15:22.325
<i>of politics on trial
that this courthouse</i>

15:22.325 --> 15:23.458
<i>has ever seen.</i>

15:23.458 --> 15:25.193
- REPORTER 1: Is that Liddy?
- REPORTER 2: Yeah, it is.

15:25.193 --> 15:28.997
- Gordon! Gordon! Gordon.
- (REPORTERS CLAMORING)

15:28.997 --> 15:30.298
LAWYER: Hey, folks.
Come on, back up!

15:30.298 --> 15:32.834
Give us some space!
Yeah, yeah. Give him some space.

15:32.834 --> 15:34.136
Hey, we've got a--
we've got a hearing

15:34.136 --> 15:35.871
in five minutes, okay?

15:35.871 --> 15:38.373
LIDDY: Hello!
Top of the morning!

15:38.373 --> 15:41.910
- (INDISTINCT CHATTER)
- LIDDY: Hello!

15:41.910 --> 15:43.846
Are you sure you don't want me
to be there?

15:43.846 --> 15:45.713
Oh, no, no, no.

15:45.713 --> 15:49.450
I'm going to act like a jackass,
piss off the prosecution,

15:49.450 --> 15:52.522
force a few errors,
take the whole thing to appeals

15:52.522 --> 15:54.226
and get it all thrown out.

15:54.859 --> 15:55.958
Seeing you in the gallery,

15:55.958 --> 15:57.827
I might be forced
to remember my manners.

15:57.827 --> 15:59.862
(FRAN SCOFFS)

15:59.862 --> 16:01.700
(CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICK)

16:03.701 --> 16:06.068
- Good Morning, gentlemen!
- REPORTER 2: Morning, Gordon.

16:06.068 --> 16:07.135
Good morning!

16:07.135 --> 16:09.300
Gordon, could you give us
a statement?

16:09.300 --> 16:10.709
Yes, I could.

16:12.010 --> 16:14.246
Come in, please. Get this down.

16:14.913 --> 16:16.078
My statement

16:16.078 --> 16:19.347
is that I have nothing
whatsoever to state.

16:19.347 --> 16:21.616
- (INDISTINCT CHATTER)
- (LAUGHS)

16:21.616 --> 16:24.153
REPORTER 3: Mr. Hunt. Howard!
Howard! Mr. Hunt.

16:24.153 --> 16:25.387
Howard,
how are you gonna plead?

16:25.387 --> 16:27.422
REPORTER 4: Mr. Hunt,
did the White House know?

16:27.422 --> 16:29.720
My client is a patriot
and a veteran

16:29.720 --> 16:31.426
who served his country
in wartime!

16:31.426 --> 16:34.029
He is here to be judged
by a jury of his peers.

16:34.029 --> 16:36.531
(REPORTERS CLAMOR)

16:36.531 --> 16:38.166
JUDGE JOHN SIRICA: <i>We are back
on the record</i>

16:38.166 --> 16:42.304
in the matter of criminal case
number 1827-72.

16:42.304 --> 16:44.105
The United States of America

16:44.105 --> 16:46.775
versus George Gordon Liddy
et al.

16:46.775 --> 16:49.244
Mr. Silbert, are you prepared
with your opening statement?

16:49.244 --> 16:51.013
Yes, I am, Your Honor.

16:51.013 --> 16:54.482
This jury is gonna wanna know
the purpose.

16:54.482 --> 16:58.086
What did these men go
into the headquarters for?

16:58.086 --> 17:02.261
Was their sole purpose
political espionage?

17:02.994 --> 17:04.163
Were they paid?

17:04.929 --> 17:07.630
Were there financial gains?

17:07.630 --> 17:08.798
