32:28.417 --> 32:31.152
Apparently, the buck stops
with me, too.

32:31.152 --> 32:34.084
McCord just tossed Dean
under the microscope.

32:34.084 --> 32:38.493
So, how is that fair-haired fuck
supposed to protect us now?

32:38.493 --> 32:40.129
SENATOR BAKER: <i>And now
Mr. McCord.</i>

32:40.129 --> 32:41.363
<i>Did you-- did you engage</i>

32:41.363 --> 32:44.399
<i>in any other break-ins
or wire taps on your own</i>

32:44.399 --> 32:47.402
<i>or with-- with Mr. Hunt,
uh, Mr. Liddy</i>

32:47.402 --> 32:49.537
<i>or others such as
the break-in,</i>

32:49.537 --> 32:52.642
<i>uh, in Mr. Ellsberg's
psychiatrist office.</i>

32:52.642 --> 32:53.743
MCCORD: <i>I did not.</i>

32:53.743 --> 32:55.480
<i>Did you receive any money?</i>

32:56.080 --> 32:57.741
<i>Yes, I did.</i>

32:57.741 --> 33:00.515
<i>I received 3,000 dollars
a month,</i>

33:00.515 --> 33:02.284
<i>which the others
received as well.</i>

33:02.284 --> 33:04.319
- (DOORBELL RINGS)
- David, could you get the door!

33:04.319 --> 33:06.055
SAM DASH: <i>And from whom
did you receive that money?</i>

33:06.055 --> 33:08.924
<i>The wife of E. Howard Hunt,
Mrs. Hunt.</i>

33:08.924 --> 33:10.158
Holy shit.

33:10.158 --> 33:11.726
<i>Did you have any knowledge, information,</i>

33:11.726 --> 33:14.797
<i>or belief as to from where
this money came from?</i>

33:14.797 --> 33:16.031
<i>I was told it came</i>

33:16.031 --> 33:17.900
<i>from the Committee
to Re-Elect the President</i>

33:17.900 --> 33:19.201
<i>by Mrs. Hunt.</i>

33:19.201 --> 33:21.069
DAVID: <i>Lisa! Saint! Help!</i>

33:21.069 --> 33:25.273
David? David!
What the fuck! Where is he?

33:25.273 --> 33:26.775
- ST. JOHN: David!
- BUCKLEY: Don't be afraid.

33:26.775 --> 33:28.977
- I'm a dear friend
of your father and you've--
- Mr. Buckley!

33:28.977 --> 33:30.645
Mr. Buckley, what are you doing?
Let go of him!

33:30.645 --> 33:34.016
My dear Lisa.
Your father wishes that David

33:34.016 --> 33:37.018
sojourn with his godfather,
Dr. Artime,

33:37.018 --> 33:39.421
in Miami during
his incarceration.

33:39.421 --> 33:40.822
What? Miami?

33:40.822 --> 33:43.391
And as your godfather,
I am here

33:43.391 --> 33:46.431
to smooth the transition
to the good doctor.

33:47.527 --> 33:48.831
DR. ARTIME: David!

33:48.831 --> 33:50.365
I have a toy for you!

33:50.365 --> 33:51.900
What are you talking about?
You can't just

33:51.900 --> 33:53.302
take him away from us.

33:53.302 --> 33:56.305
David's not going anywhere!
This is our house.

33:56.305 --> 33:59.374
Not anymore. Your father sold
the house.

33:59.374 --> 34:01.910
- (DAVID SCREAMS)
- Let go of him.
Let go of him. Stop!

34:01.910 --> 34:03.112
- Lisa!
- LISA: David!

34:03.112 --> 34:04.612
- DAVID: Help me!
- ♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

34:04.612 --> 34:08.083
- Lisa! Lisa!
- DR. ARTIME: <i>¡Muchacho!</i>

34:08.083 --> 34:11.086
You ready
for your big adventure?

34:11.086 --> 34:14.156
<i>Liddy and Hunt are convicted
Watergate conspirators</i>

34:14.156 --> 34:17.092
<i>and have been identified
as the men who burglarized</i>

34:17.092 --> 34:19.660
<i>the office of Daniel Ellsberg's
psychiatrist</i>

34:19.660 --> 34:23.465
<i>as part of an investigation
ordered by President Nixon.</i>

34:23.465 --> 34:26.135
<i>Meanwhile the Federal Court
took possession of files</i>

34:26.135 --> 34:28.203
<i>that former presidential
counsel John Dean,</i>

34:28.203 --> 34:29.704
<i>removed from the White House.</i>

34:29.704 --> 34:32.040
<i>Again today as he has so often
in the past,</i>

34:32.040 --> 34:34.076
<i>the president sought to blame
John Dean</i>

34:34.076 --> 34:35.778
<i>for the White House part,
if any,</i>

34:35.778 --> 34:37.212
<i>in the Watergate cover-up.</i>

34:37.212 --> 34:39.481
<i>News secretary Ronald Ziegler
was sent out to emphasize</i>

34:39.481 --> 34:41.049
<i>that among
top White House aides,</i>

34:41.049 --> 34:43.351
<i>Dean and Dean alone
had the responsibility</i>

34:43.351 --> 34:44.619
<i>for what was supposed
to have been</i>

34:44.619 --> 34:47.392
<i>Mr. Nixon's
own personal investigation.</i>

34:47.859 --> 34:49.058
(HOWARD COUGHS)

34:49.058 --> 34:51.226
LISA: How could you
let them take David?

34:51.226 --> 34:52.694
He was hysterical!

34:52.694 --> 34:56.799
HOWARD: Now, hold on. He'll be
well taken care of. He's safe.

34:56.799 --> 34:59.404
(COUGHS, CLEARS THROAT)

35:00.604 --> 35:03.771
I have some really good news
for all of us.

35:03.771 --> 35:07.871
My editor says that there is
considerable interest

35:07.871 --> 35:10.913
in me writing
under my own name now.

35:10.913 --> 35:12.651
How is that good news?

35:13.484 --> 35:16.886
A rising tide lifts all Hunts.

35:16.886 --> 35:19.154
That is a giant bullshit lie, man.

35:19.154 --> 35:23.091
No. One thing I will never,
ever do

35:23.091 --> 35:25.695
is lie to my children again.

35:25.695 --> 35:27.724
ST. JOHN: I'm out of here.

35:27.724 --> 35:29.498
You think you're some super spy?

35:29.498 --> 35:30.598
You're not.

35:30.598 --> 35:33.229
You're just a patsy
doing somebody else's jail time.

35:33.229 --> 35:36.875
- Good luck with the novel, Papa.
- HOWARD: Saint! St. John!

35:37.908 --> 35:39.408
Saint! Come back here!

35:39.408 --> 35:40.876
What does he want from me?

35:40.876 --> 35:43.882
Did it ever occur to you
that maybe you were wrong?

35:45.783 --> 35:46.548
Hmm?

35:46.548 --> 35:48.484
That the Democrats
weren't in cahoots

35:48.484 --> 35:50.986
with the Russians or Castro?

35:50.986 --> 35:52.755
That you,
you were the only ones

35:52.755 --> 35:55.190
- breaking the law?
- If you believe that,

35:55.190 --> 35:57.159
then your mother died
for nothing!

35:57.159 --> 36:00.662
They killed Mama!
Don't you get it?

36:00.662 --> 36:03.999
- People are writing about it.
- So then we're all in danger!

36:03.999 --> 36:05.700
And you want me
to go spouting off

36:05.700 --> 36:09.237
about the president?
You want them to kill you?

36:09.237 --> 36:10.772
David? All of us?

36:10.772 --> 36:15.447
Anyway, your mother's death,
God rest her soul,

36:16.013 --> 36:18.450
was a tragic accident.

36:19.250 --> 36:21.954
She was a patriot...

36:23.487 --> 36:25.386
- like me.
- LISA: Yeah, well,

36:25.386 --> 36:28.393
while you're in here
saluting your precious flag...

36:29.426 --> 36:32.093
John Dean is talking
to the prosecutors.

36:32.093 --> 36:33.295
What?

36:33.295 --> 36:35.467
Guess he wanted
to stay out of prison.

36:36.934 --> 36:37.937
Then again...

36:38.836 --> 36:40.405
his wife is still alive.

36:42.974 --> 36:44.376
(COUGHS)

36:45.176 --> 36:50.145
Lisa. (COUGHS) Lisa!

36:50.145 --> 36:51.847
LIDDY: I'll take a look
at your appeal.

36:51.847 --> 36:53.648
Okay. Just, uh--

36:53.648 --> 36:56.151
Thank you. Just don't forget
about the kosher meal.

36:56.151 --> 36:58.987
Oh, I will petition
the warden posthaste.

36:58.987 --> 37:00.121
- Thank you.
- Gordon.

37:00.121 --> 37:01.793
How was the visit
with the family?

37:03.895 --> 37:05.126
Dean made a deal.

37:05.126 --> 37:08.764
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

37:08.764 --> 37:10.230
LIDDY: <i>Scheisse!</i>

37:11.469 --> 37:13.063
Where's the Cubans?

37:13.063 --> 37:16.271
Uh, Danbury. Transferred.
Sturgis, too.

37:16.271 --> 37:17.940
Left this morning
while you were gone.

37:17.940 --> 37:19.844
I didn't get to say goodbye.

37:21.513 --> 37:22.681
No. No!

37:23.909 --> 37:26.418
It's just you and me, amigo.

37:29.020 --> 37:31.456
Yeah. Just us.

37:32.189 --> 37:34.254
Vladimir and Estragon.

37:36.160 --> 37:37.596
Are those Russkies?

37:38.897 --> 37:39.795
Sure.

37:39.795 --> 37:41.696
<i>I told the President
that I had gone</i>

37:41.696 --> 37:44.266
<i>to the prosecutors.
And that I did not believe</i>

37:44.266 --> 37:46.068
<i>that this was an act
of disloyalty,</i>

37:46.068 --> 37:49.204
<i>but rather in the end
it would be an act of loyalty.</i>

37:49.204 --> 37:50.372
<i>I told Haldeman</i>

37:50.372 --> 37:52.507
<i>about the meeting
in Mitchell's office.</i>

37:52.507 --> 37:54.510
<i>The President,
almost from the outset</i>

37:54.510 --> 37:55.777
<i>began asking me a number</i>

37:55.777 --> 37:57.346
<i>- of leading questions...</i>
- INMATE: Look at that

37:57.346 --> 38:00.515
fine, blonde piece of ass
Dean is fucking.

38:00.515 --> 38:03.051
- (LIDDY SHUSHES)
- GUARD: Hey! Keep it down.

38:03.051 --> 38:05.354
We're trying to watch.

38:05.354 --> 38:08.190
If Dean winds up in here
with us,

38:08.190 --> 38:11.426
I was introduced
to a con in cell block D

38:11.426 --> 38:14.363
who can silence him
for two cartons of Pall Malls.

38:14.363 --> 38:17.298
Do you want to be in here
for your whole life?

38:17.298 --> 38:18.971
They couldn't trace it to me.

38:20.304 --> 38:21.837
First thing I would do

38:21.837 --> 38:25.307
is I would punch a guard
directly in the face.

38:25.307 --> 38:29.081
Second, get transferred
to solitary confinement...

38:30.148 --> 38:31.646
ipso facto,

38:31.646 --> 38:33.348
they could never trace
the hit to me

38:33.348 --> 38:34.783
nor say I had done it.

38:34.783 --> 38:39.087
And now you've just made me
an ipso fucking facto accessory

38:39.087 --> 38:40.055
to murder.

38:40.055 --> 38:42.324
<i>Which made me think
that the conversation</i>

38:42.324 --> 38:43.825
<i>was being taped.</i>

38:43.825 --> 38:46.628
<i>And that a record was being made
to protect himself.</i>

38:46.628 --> 38:50.999
- (ALL CLAMOR)
- Nixon taped himself?

38:50.999 --> 38:52.702
- There's tapes!
- (SHUSHES)

38:52.702 --> 38:56.772
These pardons
are not forthcoming!

38:56.772 --> 39:00.475
That dumb Quaker hired us
to bug the DNC,

39:00.475 --> 39:02.711
meanwhile he was taping himself!

39:02.711 --> 39:07.049
- This is all going to blow over.
- Oh, when, Gordon? How?

39:07.049 --> 39:09.051
- Dean sold us out!
- (SHUSHES)

39:09.051 --> 39:12.688
We are going to die in here!
We are never getting out!

39:12.688 --> 39:15.660
We're never...
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

39:18.329 --> 39:19.932
- (THUD)
- (INMATE GRUNTS)

39:20.399 --> 39:21.562
Howard?

39:21.562 --> 39:24.166
- INMATE: Oh, shit!
- That motherfucker's dead.

39:24.166 --> 39:25.633
Not on my watch.

39:25.633 --> 39:27.739
- ♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
- (BREATHES DEEPLY) Come on!

39:29.140 --> 39:32.144
(GRUNTS)

39:33.310 --> 39:34.579
One side, gentlemen.

39:35.314 --> 39:36.345
Medic!

39:36.345 --> 39:38.746
<i>I do not know where
that press account came from.</i>

39:38.746 --> 39:42.785
<i>The president did not come out
of his chair.</i>

39:42.785 --> 39:44.719
<i>- I have never seen...</i>
- KEVAN HUNT: Papa.

39:44.719 --> 39:46.688
<i>...the President come out
of his chair...</i>

39:46.688 --> 39:49.929
- KEVAN: Papa.
- (INDISTINCT CHATTER ON TV)

39:53.532 --> 39:54.699
HOWARD: Hi, Kevan.

39:56.166 --> 39:57.702
What are you doing here?

39:58.336 --> 39:59.738
You had a stroke.

40:00.805 --> 40:01.773
Stroke?

40:06.277 --> 40:09.581
(GROANS)
I'm so glad you came.

40:10.181 --> 40:11.813
I...

40:11.813 --> 40:17.089
truly-- I'm sorry for all
I put you through.

40:18.256 --> 40:19.758
Not sorry enough.

40:20.792 --> 40:25.097
♪ (PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

40:26.097 --> 40:27.758
HOWARD: Oh, no...

40:27.758 --> 40:30.665
No, no, no...

40:30.665 --> 40:35.904
When Mr. McCord started talking
about Mama and the money

40:35.904 --> 40:38.640
I kind of guessed what might be
in here.

40:38.640 --> 40:41.209
Please tell me
you did not read that.

40:41.209 --> 40:43.712
KEVAN: It's fascinating stuff.

40:43.712 --> 40:47.483
I mean, payoffs, names,
dollar amounts,

40:47.483 --> 40:49.518
right down to the cent.

40:49.518 --> 40:52.624
And you involved Mama,
St. John...

40:53.325 --> 40:54.493
and me?

40:55.826 --> 40:57.358
It's a wonder
you didn't have David

40:57.358 --> 40:59.595
making money drops
with his lunch box!

40:59.595 --> 41:00.996
HOWARD: Listen to me.

41:00.996 --> 41:05.301
It-- it's-- it's for
the best interests

41:05.301 --> 41:07.002
of our country.

41:07.002 --> 41:09.570
What about the best interests
of your family?

41:09.570 --> 41:13.508
- You mother wanted to help--
- Don't talk about Mama!

41:13.508 --> 41:15.777
Either you come clean
and you tell

41:15.777 --> 41:17.612
the Senate committee the truth

41:17.612 --> 41:19.714
that you were taking orders
from the White House,

41:19.714 --> 41:22.484
or I will turn this over
to the prosecutors.

41:22.484 --> 41:24.723
- ♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
- Honey, please.

41:25.423 --> 41:28.727
Listen to me. I will fix this.

41:29.761 --> 41:30.729
Kevan!

41:33.198 --> 41:34.266
Kevan!

41:38.503 --> 41:39.671
Kevan.

41:41.872 --> 41:46.641
<i>I had no prior knowledge
of the Watergate break-in,</i>

41:46.641 --> 41:49.339
<i>I neither took part in
nor knew about any</i>

41:49.339 --> 41:52.580
<i>of the subsequent cover-up
activities,</i>

41:52.580 --> 41:55.985
<i>I neither authorized
nor encouraged subordinates</i>

41:55.985 --> 42:00.823
<i>to engage in illegal
or improper campaign tactics.</i>

42:00.823 --> 42:04.660
<i>That was and that is
the simple truth.</i>

42:04.660 --> 42:06.729
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

42:06.729 --> 42:07.896
REPORTER 1: Gordon!
How does it feel

42:07.896 --> 42:10.065
to be out of prison for the day
to testify?

42:10.065 --> 42:13.803
All this just for me, eh?
(CHUCKLES)

42:13.803 --> 42:15.638
Haven't you heard?
I'm not saying anything.

42:15.638 --> 42:16.772
REPORTER 2: Gordon!
How do you feel

42:16.772 --> 42:19.011
about the president
calling you a clown?

42:20.745 --> 42:24.013
Enjoy the circus, boys! (LAUGHS)

42:24.013 --> 42:28.548
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

42:29.554 --> 42:30.855
(SIGHS)

42:33.924 --> 42:35.952
It's about the only
private space we have.

42:35.952 --> 42:37.358
That's fine. Nope.

42:37.358 --> 42:40.032
- Uh. Could, uh...
- (DOOR CLOSES)

42:40.432 --> 42:42.167
(SIGHS)

42:49.474 --> 42:50.642
Gordon.

42:51.871 --> 42:52.844
John.

42:53.611 --> 42:54.947
(CHUCKLES)

42:56.313 --> 42:58.648
Well, look, uh, like you...

42:58.648 --> 43:00.583
I was prepared to do
whatever it took

43:00.583 --> 43:02.317
to protect the president.

43:02.317 --> 43:05.357
- (SCOFFS)
- Until, well...

43:07.491 --> 43:09.524
the president called me up
to Camp David,

43:09.524 --> 43:11.894
and he tried to get me
to write a whole report,

43:11.894 --> 43:14.366
and then he started asking me
these questions...

43:15.833 --> 43:19.738
and I suddenly realized
the son of a bitch...

43:20.771 --> 43:22.207
is recording everything.

43:23.807 --> 43:26.778
He was trying to get me
to implicate myself on tape.

43:28.613 --> 43:30.073
(CHUCKLES)

43:30.073 --> 43:31.250
I mean, can you imagine?

43:34.085 --> 43:37.018
And at that moment it was like,
uh... (CLICKS TONGUE)

43:37.018 --> 43:39.754
...it was like waking
from a fever dream, Gordon.

43:39.754 --> 43:42.958
I-- I mean, here I was a--
a-- a wild-eyed fanatic,

43:42.958 --> 43:46.795
a true believer,
and the goddamned President...

43:46.795 --> 43:49.197
the almighty leader
of the conservative cause,

43:49.197 --> 43:52.267
he couldn't care less about it
or me or you or-- or the--

43:52.267 --> 43:55.537
or the law or his country
or his staff or anything

43:55.537 --> 43:57.637
other than covering his own ass.

43:59.277 --> 44:01.076
And there's something
that you need to know.

44:01.076 --> 44:04.079
If throwing me to the wolves
was his last resort

44:04.079 --> 44:06.114
you wanna know
what his first instinct was?

44:06.114 --> 44:07.749
The very first guy
that he thought

44:07.749 --> 44:10.322
to pin this whole thing on?
Give it a guess.

44:12.289 --> 44:13.258
Go on, guess.

44:16.327 --> 44:17.296
That's right.

44:17.929 --> 44:20.099
It was you, Gordon.

44:21.298 --> 44:24.427
He thought that you were
so blindly loyal,

44:24.427 --> 44:27.468
such a complete and utter sap, moron,

44:27.468 --> 44:30.940
a stooge that you would proudly
take the heat for everyone

44:30.940 --> 44:33.345
- like a good, obedient little--
- Mr. Dean?

44:34.211 --> 44:35.347
They're ready for you.

44:38.516 --> 44:39.882
See you around, Gordon.

44:39.882 --> 44:42.685
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

44:42.685 --> 44:44.756
Nice glasses, John.

44:51.262 --> 44:52.461
(DOOR CLOSES)

44:52.461 --> 44:55.734
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

44:57.101 --> 44:57.867
(GRUNTS)

44:57.867 --> 45:02.741
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

45:15.185 --> 45:17.720
LIDDY: Uh, welcome back
to the land of the living.

45:17.720 --> 45:19.755
I borrowed your book.

45:19.755 --> 45:22.827
Buckley served under me
in Mexico City.

45:23.994 --> 45:26.231
Aren't you not supposed
to tell me that?

45:29.400 --> 45:31.170
Some spook you are.

45:32.203 --> 45:34.135
I just heard Ehrlichman
and Haldeman

45:34.135 --> 45:37.176
are going to do time
for perjury.

45:38.910 --> 45:40.508
And Bud Krogh

45:40.508 --> 45:42.481
actually turned down
a plea deal.

45:43.381 --> 45:45.417
Goddamn boy scout.

45:47.017 --> 45:49.121
Krogh is a decent fellow...

45:50.415 --> 45:53.221
unlike that pantywaist Dean.

45:53.221 --> 45:55.323
I swear to God, one more word
out of his mouth,

45:55.323 --> 45:58.527
I would have embedded my pencil
in his brain.

45:58.527 --> 45:59.999
I don't doubt it.

46:00.998 --> 46:04.099
Oh, I've taken the liberty

46:04.099 --> 46:08.373
of writing up a brief diet
and exercise regimen for you.

46:09.341 --> 46:10.442
We need to talk.

46:11.403 --> 46:12.544
LIDDY: All right. (GRUNTS)

46:13.778 --> 46:14.810
<i>¿Qué pasa?</i>

46:14.810 --> 46:17.882
Colson just told
<i>Time</i> magazine...

46:18.682 --> 46:21.384
he thinks
the CIA killed Dorothy.

46:21.384 --> 46:22.518
That's bullshit.

46:22.518 --> 46:24.456
I know who really killed her.

46:29.694 --> 46:31.193
I did.

46:31.193 --> 46:33.062
- LIDDY: Hmm.
- Every choice I made,

46:33.062 --> 46:38.067
every word I said,
put her on that plane.

46:38.067 --> 46:40.906
And I've got to live
with that every minute...

46:41.706 --> 46:43.342
for the rest of my life.

46:48.046 --> 46:51.316
Hey. Dorothy made
her own choices.

46:53.952 --> 46:55.187
We all did.

46:58.222 --> 46:59.191
I lost...

47:01.426 --> 47:02.394
everything.

47:05.163 --> 47:07.399
So, what the hell
am I doing here?

47:08.966 --> 47:12.334
Who the hell are--
are we still protecting

